vqagB1swgC&pg=PA279&dq=nama+horse|title=Rivers of Blood, Rivers of Gold:Europe's Conquest of Indigenous Peoples|author=Cocker, Mark|year=2000|location=New York|edition=1st American|publisher=Grove Press|isbn=0-8021-3801-2}}\n* {{cite book|author=Crowell, Pers|title=Cavalcade of American Horses|publisher=McGraw-Hill Book Company|location=New York|year=1951|oclc=1428574}}\n* {{cite book |editor1-last=Curta| editor1-first=Florin |editor2-first=Roman |editor2-last=Kovalev |title=The other Euorope in the Middle Ages: Avars, Bulgars, Khazars and Cumans |publisher=Kononklijke Brill NY |year=2007 |isbn=978-90-0416389-8 |page=319|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_-G1L-9Zec0C&pg=PA319}}\n* {{cite book |author=Davies, Norman |authorlink=Norman Davies |title=God's Playground: A History of Poland: Volume II 1795 to the Present |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford, UK |edition=Revised |year=2005 |isbn=0-19-925340-4 }}\n* {{cite book |author= Davis, R.H.C. |authorlink= Ralph Henry Carless Davis |title= The Medieval Warhorse |publisher= Thames and Hudson |location= London |year= 1989 |isbn= 0-500-25102-9 |url= https://archive.org/details/medievalwarhorse00davi }}\n* {{cite book |author= Devereux, Frederick L |title= The Cavalry Manual of Horse Management |publisher=A. S. Barnes |location=Cranbury, NJ |year= 1979 |edition=Reprint of 1941 |isbn=0-498-02371-0}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |author=Drower, Margaret S. | title=Syria c. 1550\u20131400 BC |encyclopedia=The Cambridge Ancient History: The Middle East and the Aegean Region c. 1800\u20131380 BC Volume II Part I |edition=Third |pages=417\u2013525| publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge, UK | year=1973 |isbn=0-521-29823-7}}\n* {{cite book |author= Ebrey, Patricia Buckley, Anne Walthall, and James B. Palais |title= Pre-Modern East Asia: A Cultural, Social, and Political History |publisher= Houghton Mifflin Company|location= Boston|year= 2005 |isbn=0-618-13386-0}}\n* {{cite book |author= Edwards, E