{"title_page": "Mrs. Pakistan World", "text_new": "{{short description|Beauty pageant}}\n{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=February 2018}} \n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} \n\n{{Infobox organization \n\n|name         = Mrs. Pakistan World \n\n|image        = \n\n|image_border = \n\n|size         =  \n\n|caption      =  \n\n|map          = \n\n|msize        = \n\n|mcaption     = \n\n|motto        = Celebrate the woman in you! \n\n|formation    = 2007 \n\n|type         = [[Beauty Pageant]] \n\n|headquarters = [[Toronto]], [[Lahore]] \n\n|location     = [[Pakistan]] \n\n| membership =  \n\n|language     = [[English language|English]], [[Urdu]] \n\n|leader_title = President \n\n|leader_name  = [[Sonia Ahmed]] Since 2007.  \n\n|website      = [http://www.mrspakistan.com/ Mrs. Pakistan Official website] \n\n}} \n'''Mrs. Pakistan World''' is a [[beauty pageant]] in Canada for married women of Pakistani decent<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oyetimes.com/cinema/masala/33855-mrs-pakistan-world-2013-to-be-crowned-in-january/|title=Mrs. Pakistan World 2013 To Be Crowned In January|last=Shafiq|first=Afsheen|website=Oye! Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>. \n\n==History==\nThe [[Miss Pakistan World]]<ref>https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/others/Shanzay-Hayat-wins-Miss-Pakistan-World-2013/articleshow/22251646.cms</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bramptonguardian.com/whatson-story/6003979-mississauga-crowns-miss-pakistan/|title=Mississauga crowns Miss Pakistan|date=2012-08-27|website=BramptonGuardian.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> and Mr. Pakistan World.<ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/1572317/4-pakistan-shines-mr-ocean-2017/</ref> pageants<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://meridianartscentre.com/events/mr-and-miss-pakistan-world|title=Mr. & Miss Pakistan World|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> were launched in 2002 & 2011 by [[Sonia Ahmed]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/14-Jan-2010/Tahmena-crowned-Mrs-Pakistan-World|title=Tahmena crowned Mrs Pakistan World|date=2010-01-14|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ebuzztoday.com/interview-with-sonia-ahmed-president-of-miss-pakistan-worldmr-pakistan-world-mrs-pakistan-world-15963/|title=Sonia Ahmed Interview|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bollyspice.com/miss-pakistan-world-is-a-step-towards-showing-a-different-pakistan-sonia-ahmed/|title=\u201cMiss Pakistan World is a step towards showing a different Pakistan\u201d \u2013 Sonia Ahmed|last=developer|date=2010-03-25|website=BollySpice.com - The latest movies, interviews in Bollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> in [[Toronto]], [[Canada]]<ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/127030/miss-pakistan-world/</ref> and the Mrs. Pakistan World contest was launched in 2007<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.insidehalton.com/news-story/2988345-mother-of-three-surprised-to-be-crowned-mrs-pakistan-world/ |title = Mother of three surprised to be crowned MRS. Pakistan World|date = 18 March 2011}}</ref> with [[Misbah Yasin-Iqbal]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://old.paktribune.com/news/A-Houston-Lady-is-Mrs-Pakistan-World-2007-169697.html | title=Military Flair up Between India and Pakistan See Both Sides Blaming One Another}}</ref> being the first woman to in history to hold the title. She was also the first married Pakistani woman to enter [[Mrs. World]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.oneindia.com/2007/02/21/pakistani-women-to-participate-in-mrs-world-2007-contest-1172052377.html | title=Pak women to participate in MRS World 2007 contest| date=21 February 2007}}</ref> in 2007. Saman Hasnain Shah<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.sfweekly.com/news/san-franciscos-very-own-mrs-pakistan-world-2008/amp/ |title = San Francisco's Very Own MRS. Pakistan World 2008|date = 2 January 2008}}</ref> was the second woman to go down in history as Mrs. Pakistan World<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/news/world/girls-showcase-real-pakistan-at-beauty-pageants/articleshow/15774709.cms |title = Girls showcase '\u02dcreal' Pakistan at beauty pageants}}</ref> and she went on to represent Pakistan in [[Mrs. World]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/san-francisco-woman-crowned-mrs-pak-world-279502.html | title=San Francisco woman crowned MRS Pak World}}</ref> 2008 and [[Mrs Globe]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-san-francisco-woman-is-mrs-pakistan-world-1142744 |title = San Francisco woman is MRS Pakistan World|date = 2 January 2008}}</ref> 2009 winning 6 titles for Pakistan. To date she is the only Mrs. Pakistan World with the most wins in subtitles. In 2010, [[Tahmena Bokhari]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.yorkregion.com/news-story/1460561-vaughan-beauty-queen-a-world-of-contradictions/ | title=Vaughan beauty queen a world of contradictions| date=19 January 2010}}</ref>, the third Mrs. Pakistan World<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.siliconeer.com/past_issues/2010/march-2010/mar10-Community-News.html |title = SILICONEER &#124; COMMUNITY: News Briefs &#124; MARCH 2010 &#124; Celebrating 11 Years!}}</ref> went on to compete in Mrs. United Nations<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.socialworkersspeak.org/media/social-worker-tahmena-bokhari-wins-new-crown.html |title = Social worker Tahmena Bokhari Wins New Crown &#124; Social Workers Speak}}</ref> 2010 and became the first ever Pakistani beauty queen<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/entertainment/arts/s/1192465_mrs_pakistan_world_speaks_up_for_arts_in_the_muslim_world |title = MRS Pakistan World speaks up for arts in the Muslim world|date = 13 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/going-out/mrs-pakistan-world-speaks-up-882977|title=Mrs Pakistan World speaks up for arts in the Muslim world|last=News|first=by Manchester Evening|last2=09:01|first2=13 Feb 2010Updated03:35|date=2010-02-13|website=manchestereveningnews|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> to win<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bramptonguardian.com/news-story/6001451-pakistan-wins-first-international-pageant-title/|title=Pakistan wins first international pageant title|date=2010-11-17|website=BramptonGuardian.com|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> the first international pageant<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.opednews.com/articles/Pakistan-Wins-First-Intern-by-Sonia-Ahmed-101116-351.html |title = Pakistan Wins First International Pageant Title - Tahmena Bokhari crowned MRS. United Nations 2010}}</ref>. \n\nIn 2011, Nyla Hasan took part in a local pageant, Mrs. Yummy Mummy 2011 for married women and was declared the first runner up. [[Saiyma Haroon]], Mrs. Pakistan World 2012 was the first Pakistani married woman to win from [[Norway]] and also became the first to compete in [[Mrs. Universe]]. Thereafter [[Farah Mahmood]], Mariam Mohammad, Noor Sheheryar followed in competing in the Mrs. Universe pageant. In 2018, Usma Kashaf<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1701319/4-mrs-pakistan-usa-2018-seeking-acting-opportunities-lahore/|title=Mrs Pakistan USA 2018 seeking acting opportunities in Lahore|last=Tribune.com.pk|date=2018-05-03|website=The Express Tribune|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> was sent to Lady of Brilliancy in [[Taiwan]] and won the title \"Lady of Popularity\" for Pakistan.\n\n==Titleholders==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Representative\n! Province\n! Host City\n! Host Country\n! Placement at International Pageants\n! References\n|-\n| 2021\n| TBA\n| \n| [[Toronto]]\n|| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{n/a| Mrs. Ocean 2021}}\n|-\n| 2020\n| Ravish Zahid - Thomas\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| [[Toronto]]\n|| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{n/a| Mrs. Ocean 2020}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.itssouthasian.com/ravish-