ersies==\nIn 2016, Mrs. Pakistan World Muskan Jay<ref>https://www.samaa.tv/culture/2016/12/chaiwala-in-movie-new-images-storm-social-media/</ref><ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/1277366/cannot-afford-love-affair-right-now-arshad-khan-chaiwala/</ref><ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/1284362/shocking-chaiwala-arshad-khan-quits-showbiz/</ref> faced a controversy as she appeared in a music video with Arshad Khan<ref>https://www.parhlo.com/arshad-khan-a-k-a-chaiwala-has-decided-to-quit-showbiz/</ref> (Chaiwala), which led to Arshad Khan<ref>https://tribune.com.pk/story/1287282/promise-no-bold-scenes-chaiwala-arshad-khan-continue-career-showbiz/</ref> quitting the industry as his appearance in the photo shoot with Muskan Jay as well as in the song Beparwai did not go down well with his family. Later on he joined back the industry and apologized<ref>https://veryfilmi.com/chaiwala-apologies-fans-bold-photos/</ref> to his fans<ref>https://trending.pk/2017/01/arshad-khan-comes-short-hiatus-reveal-didnt-quit-showbiz/</ref>.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.mrspakistan.com Mrs. Pakistan World]\n\n[[Category:Women in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Beauty Pageants articles by quality]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants for people of specific ethnic or national descents]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants in Canada]]\n[[Category:Pakistani awards]]\n", "name_user": "MistyGraceWhite", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(dubiuos claim, not supported by sources)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mrs._Pakistan_World"}
